          <h3><li type="a">Temporary installation</li></h3>
          <b>It's important to not boot into WearOS after unlocking your bootloader!</b>
          <br>While your watch is in bootloader mode, flash the recovery partitions using Linux:
          <pre><code>fastboot flash recovery ~/Downloads/zImage-dtb-{{deviceNames.[0]}}.fastboot</code></pre>

          or on Windows:
          <pre><code>fastboot flash recovery %systemdrive%%homepath%\Downloads\zImage-dtb-{{deviceNames.[0]}}.fastboot</code></pre>
          Then, use the top button on the watch to select "Recovery mode" and push the bottom button to boot into AsteroidOS.
          <br>The bootlogo will popup with the message "<b>Push asteroidos.ext4 via ADB</b>" will show below the bootlogo.
          <br>Push AsteroidOS to the internal sdcard using Linux:
          <pre><code class="bash">adb push -p ~/Downloads/asteroid-image-{{deviceNames.[0]}}.ext4 /sdcard/media/0/asteroidos.ext4</code></pre>

          or using Windows:
          <pre><code class="bash">adb push -p %systemdrive%%homepath%\Downloads\asteroid-image-{{deviceNames.[0]}}.ext4 /sdcard/media/0/asteroidos.ext4</code></pre>

          Everytime you want to reboot AsteroidOS:
          <br>
          While in recovery mode use the top button on the watch to select "Recovery mode" and push the bottom button to boot into the temporary image of AsteroidOS.
